I_Inspector - Interface in presentation.epiphyte
inspectors are in charge of gathering and providing indicators value
each inspector may be specific of a component of the simulation (population, genetics, ...)
inspectors are unknown of the thing objects (epiphyte system approach)
within a given protocol, all inspectors are managed by the protocol class
most inspectors are bound to the A_Inspector abstract class which gather generic inspector function

I_Protocol - Interface in simmasto0.protocol
Protocols define the specificity of the simulation
There have to be only one protocol in the simulation
Protocols define the agents currently simulated, the inspectors used, the parameters value
Protocols trigger most of the action within the simulation, they are constructed and initialized (initProtocol) by the context creator and triggered by the step_Utick procedure, the unique @ScheduledMethod of the simulator (+ one used for display)
Most protocols are bound to the A_Protocol abstract class which gather generic function of the simulation
Each protocol is associated with a corresponding parameters set defined as a corresponding xml/txt file in the .rs directory

initProtocol() - Method in class simmasto0.protocol.A_Protocol
In short: make this method first inherit its daughters at startup, then proceed to super (which is not the case within the constructor (super must be first there)
Longer: Triggered by the context creator at the beginning of the simulation and after constructing the protocol
The procedure can be realized only after all the CASCADING INSPECTORS and headers have been defined in the subclass hierarchy i.e., contains procedure that cannot be put in the constructor to avoid the overload when subclasses use super in their constructor
